伦敦场馆Heaven面临租金上涨32万英镑的危险https://www.nme.com/news/music/london-venue-heaven-in-jeopardy-while-faceing-320000-rent-increase-3594892?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=london-venue-heaven-in-面临租金上涨 320000 的危险Liberty DunworthThu, 29 Feb 2024 13:46:24 +0000 Music NewsNewsdanceElectronicPop https://www.nme.com/?p=3594892 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> “如果你想知道为什么这么多场馆关闭。如果您想知道为什么我们正在失去更多 LGBT 场所。业主说：“房东就是你的最佳选择。”</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/london-venue-heaven-in-jeopardy-while-facing-320000-rent-increase-3594892">伦敦后的场地 Heaven 面临危险，租金上涨 32 万英镑，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/Heaven@2000x1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>著名的 LGBTQIA+ 场所 Heaven 在租金上涨 32 万英镑后面临关闭。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多： <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/2023-was-worst-year-for-venue-closures-while-no-one-in-music-industry-seems-to-care-say-mvt-3562266">MVT 表示，2023 年是“场馆关闭最糟糕的一年”，而“音乐行业似乎没有人关心”</a></strong></li></ul><p>伦敦场馆的业主在租金大幅上涨后与房东 The Arch Company 进入仲裁纠纷，这一变化使这座著名场馆面临威胁。</p><p>据<a href="https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-68408826" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>BBC</em></a>报道，此次纠纷的起因是 The Arch Company 要求每年额外增加 24 万英镑，此前该公司于 2023 年 9 月再次要求增加 8 万英镑。</p><p>此后，业主们分享了费用上涨如何使场馆陷入危险，并坚称他们被迫“公开”这场纠纷，以突显现场音乐场馆和娱乐场所面临的压力。</p><p> “如果你想知道为什么这么多场馆都关门了。如果您想知道为什么我们正在失去更多 LGBT 场地。俱乐部创始人兼 GAY 老板杰里米·约瑟夫 (Jeremy Joseph) 在帖子中写道：“房东就是房东。”</p><p> “我们已经与他们战斗了五个月，他们不愿意让步，”帖子继续说道。 “是时候向房东施加公众压力了，这不仅仅是天堂的问题，也是每个接待场所的问题，因为如果我们的租金上涨，其他场所的租金也会增加，因为在仲裁中，他们会使用其他可比较的租金来估价你的。</p><p>仲裁程序应使场地所有者和房东双方能够达成协议，而无需上法庭。话虽这么说，约瑟夫声称这个过程已经让场馆花费了接近“1万英镑的法律费用”。 </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/C30dsvhiJPV/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);"><div style="padding:16px;"><div style="background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 50%; flex-grow: 0; height: 40px; margin-right: 14px; width: 40px;"></div><div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; flex-grow: 1; justify-content: center;"><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; margin-bottom: 6px; width: 100px;"></div><div style=" background-color: #F4F4F4; border-radius: 4px; flex-grow: 0; height: 14px; width: 60px;"></div></div></div><div style="padding: 19% 0;"></div><div style="display:block; height:50px;